summary: David Tennant talks about working on gen:lock and voicing Dr. Weller. It’s absolutely amazing to have someone like David Tennant...
caption:
David Tennant talks about working on gen:lock and voicing Dr. Weller. It’s absolutely amazing to have someone like David Tennant talk so fondly of the show and the team behind it.

“I love working in animation. All you’ve got is your voice. Everything has to happen in the script and you’re just trying to create something in that moment. And then you give it away and months later you see what animation has done to it. It’s a really interesting collective experience, but collective at arm’s length. It’s like an oil painting. It happens stroke by stroke.”

summary: THE TENTH DOCTOR ADVENTURES VOLUME 03 (LIMITED EDITION)
title: THE TENTH DOCTOR ADVENTURES VOLUME 03 (LIMITED EDITION)
excerpt: David Tennant (The Doctor), Catherine Tate (Donna Noble).
description:
David Tennant and Catherine Tate reprise their roles in Doctor Who for three more audio adventures throughout time and space in The Tenth Doctor Adventures Volume 3. And they’re taking the family with them…

Jacqueline King will return as Sylvia Noble, Donna’s mother and, returning to Big Finish after an eleven-year absence, Bernard Cribbins will reprise his role as Wilfred Mott, Donna’s grandfather.

3.1 No Place by James Goss

3.2 One Mile Down by Jenny T Colgan

3.3 The Creeping Death by Roy Gill

Written By: James Goss, Jenny T Colgan, Roy Gill

Directed By: Nicholas Briggs

Audio clip and interview

The Doctor and Donna will be back in action, with three new audio adventures coming May 2019.
